# /etc/apt/sources.list — Deckhand-rewritten for Debian Bullseye EOL.
#
# Shared template used by every profile that runs on Debian Bullseye
# (or Bullseye-derived) images: at minimum the Sovol SPI-XI 2.3.3
# image lineage (Sovol Zero + Sovol SV08 Max + likely SV08 Mini) and
# any future Bullseye-shipping printer profile. Bullseye reaches
# end-of-life in August 2026; once Debian moves it to
# archive.debian.org, the stock `deb.debian.org/debian bullseye*`
# URLs stop responding and `apt update` fails.
#
# Written by Deckhand during the stock_keep flow when the conditional
# `fix_apt_sources_if_bullseye_eoled` fires (gated on
# os_codename_is("bullseye") AND apt_remote_unreachable for
# deb.debian.org). The prior sources.list is auto-snapshotted to
# /etc/apt/sources.list.deckhand-pre-<ts>; that snapshot is the
# rollback path if a user later wants to switch back (e.g. after a
# fresh-flash to Bookworm/Trixie which has no need of this template).
#
# All three sub-archives (main+updates, backports, security) are
# preserved. archive.debian.org serves them statically post-EOL —
# they don't receive new updates but existing packages are still
# installable, which is the expected behavior for users still on
# the old release.

deb http://archive.debian.org/debian bullseye main contrib non-free
deb http://archive.debian.org/debian bullseye-updates main contrib non-free
deb http://archive.debian.org/debian bullseye-backports main contrib non-free
deb http://archive.debian.org/debian-security bullseye-security main contrib non-free
